cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with one-counter automata and their languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses shortest paths in one-counter transition systems. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper involves proving tight upper bounds. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity of accepting languages by one-counter automata. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves automata and their languages.
